adGenAOSPowerMonitor.name: adGenAOSPowerMonitor

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module
Added EPS and RPS connection and delivery traps to the existing adGenAOSPowerTraps. Also, added the RO adGenAOSPowerEpsRpsTable to allow OID support for the changes in EPS/RPS state changes.

adGenAOSPowerMonitor.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adGenAOSPowerMonitor.description: The MIB module for general configuration of power monitoring options for devices with battery backup.

adGenAOSPwrRollOvrEvntSecSinceEpoch.name: adGenAOSPwrRollOvrEvntSecSinceEpoch
adGenAOSPwrRollOvrEvntSecSinceEpoch.description: The time (seconds since epoch) that a power rollover trap was generated.

adGenAOSPowerEpsRpsEntry.name: adGenAOSPowerEpsRpsEntry

adGenAOSPowerRollover.name: adGenAOSPowerRollover
adGenAOSPowerRollover.description: This trap indicates the unit has had a change in power source, either from AC to DC or back again. The SecSinceEpoch represents the time (seconds since epoch) that the rollover occured.

adGenAOSEpsConnectionChange.name: adGenAOSEpsConnectionChange
adGenAOSEpsConnectionChange.description: This trap indicates the unit has had a change in the EPS connection state.

adGenAOSEpsDeliveryChange.name: adGenAOSEpsDeliveryChange
adGenAOSEpsDeliveryChange.description: This trap indicates the unit has had a change in the EPS delivery state.

adGenAOSRpsConnectionChange.name: adGenAOSRpsConnectionChange
adGenAOSRpsConnectionChange.description: This trap indicates the unit has had a change in the RPS connection state.

adGenAOSRpsDeliveryChange.name: adGenAOSRpsDeliveryChange
adGenAOSRpsDeliveryChange.description: This trap indicates the unit has had a change in the RPS delivery state.

adGenAOSPowerFullCompliance.name: adGenAOSPowerFullCompliance
adGenAOSPowerFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement version 2 of the adGenAOSPower MIB. When this MIB is fully implemented, then such an implementation can claim full compliance.
